modules.description: This module defines a type `t` for representing JSON values, including objects, arrays, primitives, and variants. It provides functions to convert between JSON values and S-expressions, compare JSON values, and compute hash values. It is used to serialize and deserialize JSON data, enabling structured manipulation of JSON in OCaml programs.

This module defines a JSON data model with values supporting null, boolean, float, string, array, and object types. It provides functions to convert between JSON values and S-expressions, along with comparison and hashing operations for objects and arrays. It is used to represent and manipulate structured JSON data in a type-safe manner.

This module provides a comprehensive data model for working with JSON values, supporting primitives like null, boolean, float, and string, as well as structured types like arrays and objects. The core type `t` enables representation of JSON data in a type-safe way, with operations for conversion to and from S-expressions, comparison, and hashing. You can use it to parse, manipulate, and serialize structured JSON data in OCaml programs. For example, you can construct a JSON object representing a user profile and serialize it to an S-expression for further processing.
